# Step 7

Now we'll add some outcomes to our events. We'll add the outcomes after out competitors and paths.

__`index.html`__

```html
<div class="l-flexbox l-mt-10">
  <div class="l-flex-1 l-flexbox l-horizontal" ng-repeat="outcome in liveEvent.mainBetOffer.outcomes">
     <span class="text-truncate l-flex-2 l-pr-5">{{outcome.label}}</span>
     <span class="l-flex-1 l-flexbox l-align-end l-pack-end"><strong>{{outcome.odds}}</strong></span>
  </div>
</div>
```

To apply the proper colors we need to add some of our widget classes
- kw-event-outcomes: the container for our outcomes
- kw-event-outcome: the outcome element
- kw-event-outcome-label: the outcome label element
- kw-event-outcome-odds: the outcome odds element

We also add some layout classes
- l-horizontal: set the flex orientation to horizontal
- l-flex-2: set the flex value to 2
- l-mt-10: adds 10 pixels margin to the top.
- l-pack-end: aligns the element to the end of it's flex axis
- l-align-end: aligns the element to the end of it's flex cross axis

__`index.html`__

```html
<div class="kw-event-outcomes l-flexbox l-mt-10">
  <div class="kw-event-outcome l-flex-1 l-flexbox l-horizontal" ng-repeat="outcome in liveEvent.mainBetOffer.outcomes">
     <span class="kw-event-outcome-label text-truncate l-flex-2 l-pr-5">{{outcome.label}}</span>
     <span class="kw-event-outcome-odds l-flex-1 l-flexbox l-align-end l-pack-end"><strong>{{outcome.odds}}</strong></span>
  </div>
</div>
```

The labels and odds might not look great, let's fix that.
Odds are presented in whatever the thousands are called, so let's divide it by 1000

__`index.html`__

```html
{{outcome.odds/1000}}
```

We probably want the outcome labels to display the team names and draw instead of 1 X 2.
The widgetCoreController has a method to parse this based on outcome and event type, it takes the outcome object and event object
{@link /tool/js/index.html#/api/widgetCore.controller:widgetCoreController#getoutcomelabel getOutcomeLabel }

__`index.html`__

```html
{{getOutcomeLabel(outcome, liveEvent.event)}}
```

We should also make sure that we don't show the outcomes if there are too many of them, we'll limit it to 3.

__`index.html`__

```html
ng-if="liveEvent.mainBetOffer.outcomes.length <= 3"
```

If there are more then 3 outcomes we can show how many there are.

__`index.html`__

```html
<div class="l-flexbox l-expander l-flex-1 l-pack-center l-align-center"
     ng-if="liveEvent.mainBetOffer.outcomes.length > 3">
   {{liveEvent.mainBetOffer.outcomes.length }} outcomes
</div>
```
